# Cursor rules for Kyphra

The canonical set of rules for any AI assistant (Cursor, Claude Code, etc.)
working in this repo lives in `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root. **Read it first
and treat it as the source of truth.**

These are the two rules most likely to bite if forgotten:

1. Never push to remote without explicit user approval. Local-first always.
2. Never use the corporate NTT Data git identity for this repo. Use
   `AlejandroLatorre` / `latorreotero@gmail.com` only.

Everything else — role, constraints, stack, code standards, workflow — is in
`CLAUDE.md`. If you find yourself about to duplicate a rule into this file,
update `CLAUDE.md` instead.
